From: "Shamsudeen Oloungbo" <oloungbo@zajil.net>

This is indeed an encouraging development and a plus for all those involved
in the program.
It further reinforces that collaborative multidisciplinary based public
health practice should be a major focal point as we forge ahead into the
next hundred years. I would like to ask how and where the borders around the
drop-zones were defined and maintained? What quarantine measures were
incoming animal traffic(from outside the various drop zones) subjected to --
whether from outside the zones, the state of Texas or the US?
---
Shamsudeen Oloungbo
